### Step 5: The Full End-to-End Flow
"Putting it all together, this is what happens from code to production:
```
Developer pushes tag v1.0.0 to GitLab
        ↓
GitLab CI triggers automatically
        ↓
BUILD — docker build creates wdtech-property-valuation:1.0.0
        ↓
PUSH — image pushed to registry.gitlab.com/wdtech/wdtech-property-valuation
        ↓
DEPLOY — kubectl updates EKS deployment with new image
        ↓
Kubernetes pulls image from GitLab registry
        ↓
2 pods running wdtech-property-valuation:1.0.0
        ↓
API live at https://api.wdtech.com/valuate
The whole process is fully automated — no manual SSH, no manual docker pull, no downtime. Every release is traceable back to a Git tag and a specific Docker image."
